Interface Summary
IAccessGroup An access group represents a group of items that are used as a context to provide read access to one or more items.
IAccessGroupHandle Handle to an IAccessGroup.
IAccessGroupMember Represents a member of an access group which includes an item and a descriptor for the context in which the item is contained in the group.
IAddElement Represents the add-element child of a configuration-data-delta element.
IAddition Represents the addition child of an add-element within a configuration-data-delta element.
IBehaviorConfiguration A behavior configuration represents the behavior specified in the process specification/customization for a specific operation.
IConfigurationDataDeltaElement Represents a configuration-data-delta process specification XML element.
IDescription A description of an element.

IIterationHandle Handle to an IIteration.
IIterationState Represents the initial state of an iteration as defined by a process definition.
